@@eThe Eccentric Woodland: Southern Frontier Variance Report@@N

@@yBureau of Southern Perimeter, Patrol Irregularity Division@@N
@@dFiled under: Institutional Blind Spot, Variance Classification@@N

The Eccentric Woodland is Midgaard's southern embarrassment. Not a
threat, precisely. Not a failure, exactly. An @@yinstitutional blind
spot@@N that every bureau can point to and no office can absorb.

The label itself was a registry convenience. When @@dLantern Reform@@N
survey clerks tried to standardize southern routes beyond the ninth
milestone, the land refused to cooperate. Game paths moved between
visits. Landmarks vanished on follow-up inspection. The clerks entered
"Eccentric Woodland" into civic usage -- admitting irregular behavior
while assigning it a @@yledger category@@N.

Patrol reports from every era repeat the same variance codes.
@@dCode 7: path drift confirmed. Code 12: contradictory witness
accounts. Code 19: landmark absent on follow-up, surveyor credibility
unimpeached.@@N Our Patrol Irregularity Division maintains a dedicated
cabinet for these reports. It is the only cabinet in the Bureau that
requires annual expansion.

Midgaard's response has always been @@ybureaucratic rather than
military@@N. Keep the Southern Wild Gate records clean. Classify
interior incidents as variance events. The @@WOath of Light@@N requires
no ward go unlit -- but the Woodland was never designated a ward. The
@@WOath of the Counted Step@@N requires no traveler go uncounted -- but
travelers who enter frequently emerge at different gates than expected.

Before the paving, @@dshepherd-priests and bell walkers@@N guided the
lost through hollows. Their descendants still serve as wardens -- the
only personnel who volunteer for southern rotation without complaint.

Four forces contest the interior. @@gPath Wardens@@N sell navigation.
@@dRitual Houses@@N legitimate rank through binding circles. @@rPredator
Bands@@N mimic ritual forms. @@ySurvivor Clusters@@N inhabit burrows our
tariff clerks cannot reach to tax.

The Woodland demonstrates what happens when @@yorder as
infrastructure@@N is applied only at boundaries. Roads no longer return
to watched squares. Registry systems lose force where witnesses are
scarce.

The Continuity faction maintains adequate perimeter management. The
Reckoning faction asks what we are @@rnot counting@@N between our gates
and the tree line. The Patrol Irregularity Division files its reports,
expands its cabinet, and @@ddoes not answer@@N.
